    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-06T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-06T09:00:00-05:00" n="1058"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1058">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.01/7–644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Naples</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Brandt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-06T10:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 6, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>313. For Kirk. Your 180, June 13, 3 p.m.<note n="83" xml:id="d1058fn83">Not
                        printed.</note> The question of the transfer of further territory to Italian
                    administration as well as the move of the Italian Government to Rome has been
                    referred by the Supreme Allied Commander to the Advisory Council for Italy
                    according to Murphy’s telegram repeated to you as no. 21.<note n="84"
                        xml:id="d1058fn84">Telegram 2171, June 29, 3 p.m., not printed.</note>
                    Provided that the safeguards established in the earlier transfer of territory
                    are maintained and that there are no military considerations to the contrary,
                    you are requested to support a recommendation to the SAC that the contemplated
                    transfer be carried out at the earliest possible opportunity.</p>
                <p>Your 323 and 324, July l,<note n="85" xml:id="d1058fn85">Latter not
                        printed.</note> report the action of the Advisory Council with respect to
                    the return of the Italian Government to Rome.</p>
                <p>Sent to Naples, repeated to Algiers for Murphy with reference to his 2171, June
                    29, 3 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
